data.text:
The CrawsOver Pro-Am League will this year host a number of NBA stars, with Golden State Warriors aces Gary Payton II and Jonathan Kuminga.

The pair have both confirmed their involvement at the event in Seattle, with Payton returning to his home town.

The CrawsOver Pro-Am is back for a 12th occasion with the Warriors players among those taking part.

What is the CrawsOver Pro-Am League?

The CrawsOver Pro-Am League is a top-tier summer pro-am basketball league that features current and former professional, international, minor league and collegiate players.

It was founded in 2011 by 20-year NBA veteran and Seattle native Jamal Crawford, a three-time NBA Sixth Man of the Year.

The CrawsOver is played at Seattle Pacific University and is free to attend for everyone.

The league typically runs for six weeks in the summer, with games played on Saturdays and Sundays.

Last season's star-filled event

Only a year ago, the guest list of players included the likes of LeBron James, Jayson Tatum, Paolo Banchero, Chet Holmgren and Aaron Gordon.

It wasn't a great memory for Holmgren, as he suffered a foot injury which caused him to miss out on the 2022/23 season.

Both Payton and Kuminga will be making their debut in the league and hoping to make better memories.
